Kathleen Key https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kathleen_Key 0 Kathleen Key (born Kitty Lanahan, April 1, 1903 – December 22, 1954) was an American actress who achieved a brief period of fame during the silent era. She is best remembered for playing Tirzah in the 1925 film Ben-Hur. Key was a great-great granddaughter of Francis Scott Key.
